22:03.650 --> 22:04.844
Of course you do.

22:04.890 --> 22:07.552
It's to your benefit,
too. The lease.

22:07.590 --> 22:09.717
What lease? This lease?

22:09.760 --> 22:11.978
Yes, to these offices--
the 27th, 28th floor.

22:12.030 --> 22:14.851
It's still under your name,
yours and Will's, but...

22:14.900 --> 22:17.892
on his passing,
it reverted to you.

22:17.930 --> 22:21.366
And as you can see, you
no longer work here, so...

22:21.400 --> 22:25.063
we ask that you pass the lease
to Mr. Canning and myself.

22:25.110 --> 22:27.135
Really?

22:27.170 --> 22:30.742
(chuckling)

22:30.780 --> 22:32.372
I don't see what's so funny.

22:32.410 --> 22:35.072
It makes no sense for you
to act as sub-lessor.

22:35.120 --> 22:37.918
Makes no sense for you
to hold on to my e-mail,

22:37.950 --> 22:39.110
but here we are.

22:39.150 --> 22:41.618
(chuckles):
Exactly.

22:41.660 --> 22:44.686
So let's trade-- give us
the lease and here you go.

22:47.130 --> 22:48.654
No.

22:48.700 --> 22:51.089
Diane...

22:51.130 --> 22:53.121
I'll rip it up.

22:53.170 --> 22:56.594
Do it. But you'll never
get the lease.

22:56.640 --> 22:58.107
I might even kick you out.

22:58.140 --> 23:00.779
Don't call my bluff.

23:03.680 --> 23:05.545
Go ahead, David--
it's a copy

23:05.580 --> 23:07.172
of an e-mail.

23:07.210 --> 23:09.417
The paper
doesn't matter.

23:12.450 --> 23:14.054
Give me the e-mail,

23:14.090 --> 23:17.423
and I will discuss a
transfer of the lease.

23:18.460 --> 23:20.553
That is my best offer.

23:20.600 --> 23:22.022
